					<h2>Description</h2>
					<p>The stylish city of Bordeaux is an incredible place to stop to. With 350 classified buildings and nearly no stylistic changes in two centuries, Bordeaux undoubtedly deserves its UNESCO world heritage site status. <br>Renowned for its vineyards, wine certainly runs through the veins of the city and can be experienced in many ways.And with a cycling tour in Saint Emilion, be sure to have a fantastic wine experience !<br>Saint Emilion is one of the most famous viticultural center in France outside the city of Bordeaux itself, this small village is a Unesco World Heritage site thanks to its unspoiled character and its medieval monuments. Boutiques, restaurants, wineshops and hotels continue to fill its medieval streets, enticing the thirsty visitors with their wares.<br>Come to experience this Wine tasting break with Bleu Vins and uncover the secrets of Bordeaux wines !</p>
