				</div>
				<hr class="featurette-divider">
				<div id="tab2">
					<h2>Itinerary</h2>
					<b>Day 1</b><br>
Arrive at your charming Boutique Hotel in Bordeaux city centre. 
We would suggest to explore the city by night and try one of the numerous french bistrot and brasserie that you can find in the heart of the city. If you are looking for cheese and wine we will be happy to recommend some lovely wine bars to stop to.
<br><br>
<b>Day 2</b><br>
You will discover the famous vineyards of Saint-Emilion by bicyle! Enjoy a full day wine experience accompanied by your guide. You will ride along the vineyards and the famous chateaux of this region. During the day you will visit two chateaux, enjoy a lunch accompanied by wine and dicover the medieval village of Saint-Emilion, which is Unesco’s World Heritage classified. 
In the evening, feel free to look at our list of favorite restaurants and choose from traditional restaurants, wine bar, typical bistros, you do not run out of choices in this city full of great restaurants!<br><br>

<b>Day 3</b><br>
On your final day in Bordeaux, we suggest a stroll in one of the city's markets. Maybe try the "marché des Quais" in Chartrons district, one of the largest markets in Bordeaux. The atmosphere is beautiful  and guests can enjoy and taste the Bordeaux specialties, local food and good wines. 
				</div>
